# GOLS brand

Before UI, layout, marketing copy, or visual work:

1. Read [brand/tokens.json](../../brand/tokens.json)
2. Read [brand/guidelines.md](../../brand/guidelines.md) — logo, color, typography sections

## Logos

Use files under `brand/logos/` only. Paths from `tokens.json` → `logos`:

| Context | Variant / file |
|---------|----------------|
| Favicon, mobile header, compact | `primary` |
| Header/footer on light bg | `secondaryLightBg` |
| Header/footer on dark bg | `secondaryDarkBg` |
| Dark busy backgrounds | `secondaryAllWhite` |

Copy [templates/Logo.tsx.template](../../templates/Logo.tsx.template) during bootstrap. Do not stretch, rotate, or recolor logos.

## Colors

Use CSS variables from [templates/brand.css.template](../../templates/brand.css.template). Primary CTA: `--gols-cardinal-red` (`#c62128`).

**Never:** logo on Cardinal Red background; hardcoded hex outside tokens; logo over athlete faces.

## Typography

- **Oswald** — headings, all caps
- **Roboto** — body, UI, email
- **Orbitron** — display/numerals only, sparingly

Load Google Fonts per `tokens.json` → `fonts.*.googleFonts`.

## Bootstrap

When scaffolding a frontend:

- Copy `templates/brand.css.template` → `src/styles/brand.css` (import in app entry)
- Copy `templates/Logo.tsx.template` → `src/components/Logo.tsx` (adjust import paths)
- Use `<Logo />` in header; favicon from primary mark
- Run `./scripts/validate-brand`
